******
[1] USA (Washington state): pediatric death
Date: Fri 22 Jan 2016
Source: Fox 8 News [edited]
http://www.foxnews.com/health/2016/01/22/12-year-old-washington-girl-dies-from-flu.html


The family of a 12 year old girl who died after contracting the flu said her illness progressed like "a freight train".

The [girl's mother], of Kitsap County, Washington, described her daughter as a usually very healthy child, according to Fox 8. On Tuesday [12 Jan 2016], the girl presented a high fever, and her family took her to the doctor, who prescribed her Tamiflu [oseltamivir]. The girl would see the doctor 2 more times before being told to go to the hospital if symptoms did not improve.

"She continued to have high fevers just like me; it was horrible." The mother told Fox 8 that her daughter began vomiting blood, and as they were on their way to the hospital, her daughter collapsed in her arms. "Her legs were spaghetti noodles," [said the mother]. "It just went that way, and she said, 'Oh momma,' and she collapsed in my arms."

Doctors were unable to revive her. "The flu attacked her kidneys, so it caused renal failure. ... They let me lay there and hold her for hours, and they were so kind to us."

According to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC), there have been only 7 pediatric flu deaths nationwide since 4 Oct 2015, when the CDC began tracking the flu for this season.

This child is the 2nd person to die from complications from the flu this season in Kitsap County. Officials are urging others in the community to get vaccinated.

[submitted by: <memphisservices@bellsouth.net>]

