communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[This tragic case is an unfortunate reminder that vaccination against seasonal influenza is recommended for all children over 6 months of age. Approximately 90 per cent of cases occur in children who have not received a flu vaccination.

Excerpted from http://www.cdc.gov/flu/spotlights/children-flu-deaths.htm [edited]:
CDC began tracking flu-associated pediatric deaths [that is, in those under 18 years of age] after the 2003-2004 flu season -- a season that started early and was intense. In addition, it took a high toll on children. In the 2003-2004 season, 153 pediatric deaths were reported to CDC from 40 states. Flu-associated pediatric deaths became nationally reportable the following season. Since that time, reported pediatric deaths during regular influenza seasons have ranged from 35 (in 2011-2012) to 122 (in 2010-2011). However, during the 2009 H1N1 influenza pandemic, which lasted from 15 Apr 2009 to 2 Oct 2010, 348 pediatric deaths were reported to CDC.

A map of Washington state in the United States can be found at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3960019,248. - Mod.LK]

